cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.EM, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the security of USB devices and proposes a framework for analyzing USB firmware images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves software engineering aspects such as developing targeting algorithms and building lifters, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) another likely category. The paper also deals with symbolic execution, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with embedded systems, which makes cs.EM (Embedded Systems) a likely category. Finally, the paper involves programming languages and compilers, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category.
